  "prompt": "What is meaning of \u0e2b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e01\u0e25\u0e34\u0e48\u0e19\u0e08\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e4c?",
  "response": "\"\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e01\u0e25\u0e34\u0e48\u0e19\u0e08\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e23\u0e4c\" is a Thai phrase that can be translated to English as \"captivated by the scent of the moon.\" In Thai culture and literature, this phrase is often used metaphorically to describe a deep enchantment or fascination with something elusive and beautiful. It evokes imagery of being mesmerized by something ethereal and enchanting, much like the delicate scent of jasmine or other fragrant blooms that can be associated with moonlit nights. It suggests a sense of poetic longing or admiration.",
